<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="603" pageId="1" pageNumber="602" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[178,938,796,818]" box="[178,938,796,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">
D e p o s i t o r y: 
<typeStatus box="[384,478,796,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Holotype</typeStatus>
is deposied in the Zoologisk Museum, Lund.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1085,834,885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">E t y m o l o g y: The name &quot;adustior&quot; of the new species refers to the brown ground colour of the body.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1086,900,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">
D e s c r i p t i o n of the male 
<typeStatus box="[545,652,900,922]" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">holotype</typeStatus>
: Body 
<quantity box="[730,811,900,922]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="602" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
long. Antenna as long as body and with 24 antennomeres. First flagellomere twice and penultimate flagellomere 1.8 times as long as broad, flagellum attenuating. Head in dorsal view transverse (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1069,959,981]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), twice as broad as long, eye somewhat longer than temple, temple distinctly rounded, occiput weakly excavated. Temporal and hypostomal carinae meeting near to base of mandible (
<figureCitation box="[286,349,1046,1068]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Ocelli middle-sized, elliptic, OOL four times longer than POL. Eye in lateral view 1.5 times as high as wide, just wider than temple (15:14), temple somewhat narrowing ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[395,458,1105,1127]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, see arrows). Malar space somewhat longer than basal width of mandible. Face 2.3 times as wide as high, inner margin of eyes parallel. Clypeus twice as wide below as high medially, pair of tentorial pits somewhat nearer to eye than to each other, lower margin of clypeus truncate (i.e. without denticules, cf. 
<figureCitation box="[926,1007,1193,1215]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1259,1279]" captionTargetBox="[196,1078,243,1215]" captionTargetId="figure-95@9.[164,1099,187,1248]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 13-19. Diospilus subfuscus nov.sp.: (13) head in dorsal view, (14) head in lateral view, (15) clypeus in frontal view, (16) propodeum, (17) hind femur, (18) distal part of right forewing, (19) tergites 1-3. Figs 20-22: Topaldios subparallelus nov.sp.: (20) head in dorsal view, (21) head in lateral view, (22) hind femur. Figs 23-24: Topaldios porrectus PAPP: (23) head in dorsal view, (24) hind femur." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328225/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Head polished, face with hair-punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1086,1259,1457]" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">
Mesosoma in lateral view 1.5 times as long as high, polished. Pronope invisible (head concealing pronotum due to the mounting position). Notaulix evenly deep, crenulated. Prepectal carina distinct. Precoxal suture fairly wide, crenulated. Areolation of propodeum distinct, areola basalis narrow, pair of spiracles latero-anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1005,1073,1347,1369]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Hind femur thick, 2.8 times as long as broad medially (
<figureCitation box="[741,803,1377,1399]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Hind tibial spurs short, as long as fourth tarsomere. Hind basitarsus somewhat shorter than tarsomeres 2-3 combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1085,1472,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">
Forewing as long as body. Pterostigma (
<figureCitation box="[593,655,1472,1494]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) less wide, 3.6 times as long as wide and issuing 
<emphasis box="[257,267,1503,1524]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">r</emphasis>
proximally from its middle, 
<emphasis box="[568,578,1503,1524]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">r</emphasis>
very short; 
<emphasis box="[704,753,1502,1524]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">1-R1</emphasis>
reaching tip of wing, 
<emphasis box="[984,1034,1502,1524]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">2-R1</emphasis>
very short: 0.1 times as long as 
<emphasis box="[458,505,1531,1553]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">1-R1</emphasis>
. Second submarginal cell narrow, i.e. 
<emphasis box="[906,956,1531,1553]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">3-SR</emphasis>
0.6 times as long as 
<emphasis box="[259,295,1561,1582]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">r-m</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[308,357,1560,1582]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">2-SR</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[408,444,1561,1582]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">r-m</emphasis>
parallel, 
<emphasis box="[541,582,1560,1582]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">SR1</emphasis>
faintly bent and five times as long 
<emphasis box="[946,995,1560,1582]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">3-SR</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1009,1072,1560,1582]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="602">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1085,218,270]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">
First discal cell relatively high, 
<emphasis box="[505,547,218,240]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">1-M</emphasis>
twice as long as 
<emphasis box="[725,775,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">m-cu</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[789,838,218,240]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">1-SR</emphasis>
indistinct, 
<emphasis box="[955,1034,218,240]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">1-SR-M</emphasis>
onesixth shorter than 
<emphasis box="[360,402,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">1-M</emphasis>
; first subdiscal cell distally closed (
<figureCitation box="[766,827,248,270]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
, see arrow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1085,285,395]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">
First tergite broad, slightly (1.1 times) longer than broad posteriorly, twice broader behind than basally; pair of spiracles before middle of tergite, pair of basal keels near to lateral margin of tergite, hind part of tergite with fine striolation (
<figureCitation box="[871,937,343,365]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Tergites 2-3 equal in length, together with further tergites polished.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1085,410,520]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Scape and pedicel yellowish, flagellum brown. Head blackish brown, mesosoma dark brown, metasoma brown. Palps and mandible straw yellow. Clypeus brown, face dark brown. Tegula yellowish. Legs yellow, coxae and trochanters straw yellow, hind tibia entirely brown. Wings hyaline, pterostigma brown, venation light brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,451,535,557]" box="[178,451,535,557]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Female and host unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,515,572,594]" box="[178,515,572,594]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">
D i s t r i b u t i o n: 
<collectingCountry box="[410,512,572,594]" name="Honduras" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Honduras</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1086,610,1025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">
T a x o n o m i c p o s i t i o n: The new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2012" box="[740,931,610,632]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Diospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adustior">
<emphasis box="[740,931,610,632]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Diospilus adustior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is near to 
<taxonomicName authority="PAPP" authorityName="PAPP (PAPP" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Diospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podobe">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">D. podobe</emphasis>
PAPP
</taxonomicName>
by their dark body colour and broad first tergites (
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP J" box="[861,1032,639,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref5443" refString="PAPP J. (1995): New diospiline taxa from the Neotropical Region (Hymenoptera, Braconidae: Helconinae). - Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 41 (2): 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1995">PAPP 1995: 106</bibRefCitation>
), the male of the two species are distinguished as follows: 1 (2) Head in dorsal view less transverse, 1.75 times as broad as long, eye somewhat shorter than temple (Fig. 8). First tergite somewhat broader posteriorly than long, 2.2 times broader behind than basally (Fig. 9). Propodeum: areola basalis wide, its carination as in Fig. 10. Hind femur 3.3 times as long as broad medially (Fig. 11). Forewing: pterostigma wide, 2.6 times as long as wide, 
<emphasis box="[775,814,792,813]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">SR1</emphasis>
approaching tip of wing, 
<emphasis box="[231,277,815,836]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">2-R1</emphasis>
long: 0.25 times as long as 
<emphasis box="[547,593,815,836]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">1-R1</emphasis>
(Fig. 12). Antenna with 28 antennomeres. Head and mesosoma black.: 
<quantity box="[475,551,837,858]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="603" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[560,668,837,858]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[677,771,837,858]" name="Honduras" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Honduras</collectingCountry>
................ 
<taxonomicName authority="PAPP 1995" authorityName="PAPP (PAPP" authorityYear="1995" box="[877,1085,837,858]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Diospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podobe">
<emphasis box="[877,978,837,858]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">D. podobe</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP J" box="[984,1085,837,858]" pageId="2" pageNumber="603" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref5443" refString="PAPP J. (1995): New diospiline taxa from the Neotropical Region (Hymenoptera, Braconidae: Helconinae). - Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 41 (2): 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1995">PAPP 1995</bibRefCitation>
