2 (1) Head in dorsal view transverse, twice as broad as long, eye somewhat longer than temple (
<figureCitation box="[313,373,891,912]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). First tergite somewhat longer than broad posteriorly, nearly twice broader behind than basally (
<figureCitation box="[513,572,914,935]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Propodeum: areola basalis narrow, its carination as in 
<figureCitation box="[289,351,936,957]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Hind femur 2.8 times as long as broad medially (
<figureCitation box="[875,938,936,957]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Forewing: pterostigma less wide, 3.6 times as long as wide, 
<emphasis box="[709,748,959,980]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">SR1</emphasis>
reaching tip of wing, 
<emphasis box="[963,1009,959,980]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">2-R1</emphasis>
very short: 01 times as long as 
<emphasis box="[496,543,982,1003]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">1-R1</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[559,621,982,1003]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1442,1462]" captionTargetBox="[209,1063,255,1408]" captionTargetId="figure-2@8.[178,1085,212,1431]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1-7: Diospilus adustior nov.sp.: (1) head in dorsal view, (2) hind ventral view of head, (3) head in lateral view, (4) propodeum, (5) hind femur, (6) distal part of right forewing, (7) tergites 1- 3. Figs 8-12: Diospilus podobe PAPP: (8) head in dorsal view, (9) first tergite, (10) propodeum, (11) hind femur, (12) distal part of right forewing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="603">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Antenna with 24 antennomeres. Head and mesosoma brown.: 
<quantity box="[443,519,1004,1025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="603" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. 
